snippet: Working-age Americans are seeing the doctor less, but how much this has to do with the economy and how much with changing demographics is unclear.
abstract: Census Bureau reports that working-age Americans are going to to the doctor less frequently than they were 10 years ago; officials say possible reasons for the decline include the poor economy and changing demographics.
lead_paragraph: Working-age Americans are seeing the doctor less, but how much this has to do with the economy and how much with changing demographics is unclear.

headline.main: Doctor Visits Dropping, New Census Figures Show
headline.print_headline: Doctor Visits Dropping, New Census Figures Show
